{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idc4392f91-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87","identifier":"/us/usc/t38/s8521"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"8521"},"text":"§ 8521.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" Presumption of contract for disposition of personalty","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The fact of death of a veteran (admitted as such), or a dependent or survivor of a veteran receiving care under the penultimate sentence of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s1781/b"},"text":"section 1781(b) of this title","children":[],"tail":", in a facility or hospital, while being furnished care or treatment therein by the Department, leaving no spouse, next of kin, or heirs, shall give rise to a conclusive presumption of a valid contract for the disposition in accordance with this subchapter, but subject to its conditions, of all property described in "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t38/s8520"},"text":"section 8520 of this title","children":[],"tail":" owned by said decedent at death and as to which such person dies intestate."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idc4392f92-47c4-11f1-bf59-9680b1269b87"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/85/857"},"text":"Pub. L. 85–857","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1958-09-02"},"text":"Sept. 2, 1958","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/72/1260"},"text":"72 Stat. 1260","children":[],"tail":", § 5221; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/94/581/tII/s208/c"},"text":"Pub. L. 94–581, title II, § 208(c)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1976-10-21"},"text":"Oct. 21, 1976","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/90/2860"},"text":"90 Stat. 2860","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/99/576/tVII/